slurm.sh and slurm_submit.sh are for running on a nersc machine

1. go to the working directory: cd $SCRATCH

2. create a project directory under the working directory

3. copy the executable and slurm.sh on the project directory

4. create a run directory under the project directory

5. copy inputs_dimerization_giant_fluct and slurm_submit.sh on the run directory

6. submit a job: ./slurm_submit.sh
